WEBVTT

00:07.887 --> 00:09.218
Uh, could you give us
a second?

00:09.219 --> 00:10.992
The Skitters must have
changed the frequency

00:11.026 --> 00:13.327
that they're using
for communications again.

00:13.361 --> 00:15.193
When we find the right signal,
with any luck,

00:15.227 --> 00:17.326
we should be able to stop
the Skitters and Mechs,

00:17.360 --> 00:18.626
well,
right in their tracks.

00:18.660 --> 00:20.894
Hey.
I'm glad you're here.

00:20.928 --> 00:23.126
Ben says that when
he hears the signal, it hurts.

00:23.160 --> 00:24.794
After everything
he's been through,

00:24.828 --> 00:26.366
I don't want to make it
any worse.

00:26.400 --> 00:29.202
I wish I could tell you
what the effects might be,

00:29.236 --> 00:31.038
but we're
in new territory.

00:31.072 --> 00:33.273
Sounds like you think Scott's jamming
idea might actually work.

00:33.308 --> 00:34.942
Well, he's hopeful.

00:34.977 --> 00:37.914
Hail Mary passes seem to be
the order of the day.

00:37.949 --> 00:41.184
Setting gun positions
and barricades

00:41.219 --> 00:43.087
and coming up
with an evacuation plan --

00:43.122 --> 00:46.858
it's a long way
from the lecture hall.

00:46.892 --> 00:50.196
Tom, I know you're worried
about Hal, but he's smart.

00:50.231 --> 00:52.966
If Weaver's mission isn't right,
he'll back off.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.269
Oh, he's 16 and he's hurting
and he wants payback.

00:55.303 --> 00:57.237
He's gonna see this through,
if he can.

00:57.272 --> 00:59.273
How can you be sure?

00:59.307 --> 01:00.541
Because <i>I</i> would.

01:02.076 --> 01:03.943
No, if Weaver
sticks to Porter's timeline,

01:03.978 --> 01:05.379
they'll go in
just after dark.

01:05.413 --> 01:06.846
That's eight hours.

01:06.881 --> 01:08.247
I just want to
get through this day.

01:08.282 --> 01:09.916
Oh, for love of --

01:09.950 --> 01:12.017
the generator
must have run out of gas.

01:12.051 --> 01:13.752
I told those kids
at the motor pool

01:13.786 --> 01:15.152
to make sure
it was full up.

01:15.186 --> 01:16.753
I think there's a spare can
in the store room.

01:16.788 --> 01:18.221
Ben, you want to
give me a hand?

01:18.255 --> 01:21.023
Yeah, sure.

01:23.294 --> 01:24.994
I-I'm gonna head back
to the clinic,

01:25.029 --> 01:26.062
unless you need me.

01:26.097 --> 01:27.931
No, no.
I'm good. I'm good.

01:27.966 --> 01:29.966
Thanks.

